{"cursor":"9476","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox Political post |post =Chief Justice |body =Canada |nativename\n= Juge en chef du Canada |insignia = |insigniasize =110px\n|insigniacaption =Coat of Arms of Canada |department = |image =Beverley\nMcLachlin.jpg |alt =The Chief Justice of Canada |incumbent =Beverley McLachlin,\nPC |incumbentsince =7 January 2000 |style =The Right Honourable\n|residence = |nominator =Prime Minister of Canada |appointer =Governor-General\nof Canada |termlength =No set term, though retirement is mandatory at age 75\n|inaugural =Sir William Buell Richards |formation =30 September 1875 |last =\n|abolished = |succession =Assumes viceregal duties upon the death or\nincapacitation of the Governor-General |deputy = |salary = $370,300\n|website = [http://scc-csc.gc.ca/home-accueil/index-eng.asp Supreme Court] }}\n\n\nThe 'Chief Justice of Canada', like the eight puisne Justices of the Supreme\nCourt of Canada, is appointed by the Governor-in-Council (Governor General of\nCanada on the advice of the Cabinet). All nine are chosen from either sitting\njudges or barristers who have at least ten years' standing at the bar of a\nprovince or territory. The Chief Justice is sworn as a member of the Queen's\nPrivy Council for Canada prior to taking the oath of office as Chief Justice.\n","linknr":318,"url":"List_of_Chief_Justices_of_the_Supreme_Court_of_Canada","recorded":1375066029,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Chief_Justice_of_Canada&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Chief_Justice_of_Canada&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Chief_Justice_of_Canada","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediaw